08/11/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Any discussions about Kosovo's decentralisation would be based in Pristina, according to UNMIK public relations chief Hua Jiang. 
In a statement Sunday (7 November), she repeated UNMIK's stance that Kosovo Serbs should participate in the process. 
Jiang added that UNMIK head Soren Jessen-Petersen wants the working group for decentralisation to meet as soon as possible. 
(Danas, Beta, B92 - 08/11/04)
